data.title: David Wanja - 2007-08 - Men's Tennis
data.meta_description: David Wanja -                     2005-06 (So.): Sat out the 2006 spring            season due to injury.             2004-05 (So.): Posted a 2-1 record in singles
data.text:
2005-06 (So.): Sat out the 2006 spring season due to injury.

2004-05 (So.): Posted a 2-1 record in singles play in the spring, going 1-1 at the No. 6 spot and 1-0 at the No. 3 ... Was 0-1 in Southland Conference play ... Posted a 6-5 record in doubles with Christian Olivier ... Went 5-5 at No.3 and 1-0 at No. 2 ... Went 3-3 in SLC play in doubles.

Previous College: Played one year at Texas Lutheran University in Seguin, Texas ... Recorded a 5-5 singles record at the No. 4 ... Also posted a 7-2 record at No. 2 doubles ... Earned one conference `Player of the Week' honor.

High School: Attended Katy High School in Katy, Texas ... Was a two-time team MVP and also served as co-captain as a senior ... Named `Most Improved' as a sophomore ... Two-time academic all-district honoree.
